# Rule: Dynamic Data Binding

**Scope:** Any UI text describing a data range, total, or other value
derived from fetched data.

**Rule:** Such text must be computed from the fetched data (or its
metadata) at render time — never hardcoded as a literal string.

**Rationale:** `DashboardHeader` is passed `period="2024 - Full Year"`
as a hardcoded string, but the backend generates a rolling 12-month
window from `date.today()`. This was invisible from reading the code
alone and only surfaced by running the app — the chart x-axis showed
Aug 2025 → Jun 2026 against a "2024" header.

**Compliant example:** The header period is derived from the min/max
`create_date` in the fetched movements (the existing
`/api/metrics/facets` endpoint already returns this).

**Non-compliant example:** Current state —
`<DashboardHeader period="2024 - Full Year" />`.